abstract: Profit declined 7.8 percent partly because of the health law and the high costs of a hepatitis C treatment.
snippet: Profit declined 7.8 percent partly because of the health law and the high costs of a hepatitis C treatment.
lead_paragraph: The UnitedHealth Group, one of the nation’s largest health insurers, reported lower earnings on Thursday, attributing its weak results in part to the federal health care law.
